EEG Dipole Demo: Coronal Slice + Scalp Topomap

Place one or more current dipoles inside a simplified head/brain model and observe the predicted scalp potential pattern. Computation uses a point-dipole approximation in a homogeneous conductive medium: V ∝ (p · R) / |R|³, summed over dipoles.

Selected dipole controls

EEG / Topomap options

Higher = smoother but slower.
Interaction
  • Click a dipole to select it; drag to move.
  • Drag the small handle at the arrowhead to rotate.
  • Keyboard: Delete removes selected; A/D rotate; W/S change amplitude.
Intended for conceptual teaching (not a full forward model). Units are arbitrary; patterns and polarity are the key learning objective.
